🤖 What is a GitHub Copilot Agent?
A Copilot Agent is an AI-powered autonomous assistant that goes far beyond inline code suggestions — it can plan, reason, write, run, and self-correct across your entire codebase.
Traditional Copilot
Inline autocomplete
Single-line or block suggestions
Reactive — waits for you to type
No awareness of test results
Copilot Agent
Multi-step autonomous execution
Reads, writes, and runs across files
Proactive — iterates until tests pass
Understands your full project context
🏗️ How to Set Up the Copilot Agent
✅
Prerequisites: GitHub Copilot Business or Enterprise license · VS Code with Copilot Chat extension (v1.150+) · Node.js + Playwright installed

Step 1 — Enable Agent Mode in VS Code

Open the Copilot Chat panel
Switch from Ask mode → Agent mode via the dropdown
Step 2 — Give it Context

Open your component file (e.g. Button.tsx)
Reference files using #file: or @workspace
Step 3 — Issue a Natural Language Task

@workspace Generate a Playwright component test for the LoginForm component.
Cover: valid login, invalid credentials, empty fields, and loading state.
Step 4 — Agent Execution Loop

flowchart LR
  A["Read Component Source"] --> B["Identify Props & States"]
  B --> C["Write .spec.ts Test File"]
  C --> D["Run Playwright Tests"]
  D --> E{"Tests Pass?"}
  E -- No --> F["Read Failures & Self-Correct"]
  F --> C
  E -- Yes --> G["✅ Done"]
🎭 What It Generates: Playwright Component Tests
Given a LoginForm.tsx, the agent autonomously produces:

import { test, expect } from '@playwright/experimental-ct-react';
import LoginForm from './LoginForm';

test.describe('LoginForm', () => {

  test('renders and submits valid credentials', async ({ mount }) => {
    const component = await mount(<LoginForm />);
    await component.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');
    await component.getByLabel('Password').fill('password123');
    await component.getByRole('button', { name: 'Login' }).click();
    await expect(component.getByText('Welcome')).toBeVisible();
  });

  test('shows error on invalid credentials', async ({ mount }) => {
    const component = await mount(<LoginForm />);
    await component.getByLabel('Email').fill('wrong@example.com');
    await component.getByLabel('Password').fill('wrongpass');
    await component.getByRole('button', { name: 'Login' }).click();
    await expect(component.getByText('Invalid credentials')).toBeVisible();
  });

  test('disables submit when fields are empty', async ({ mount }) => {
    const component = await mount(<LoginForm />);
    await expect(component.getByRole('button', { name: 'Login' }))
      .toBeDisabled();
  });

  test('shows loading state on submit', async ({ mount }) => {
    const component = await mount(<LoginForm />);
    await component.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');
    await component.getByLabel('Password').fill('password123');
    await component.getByRole('button', { name: 'Login' }).click();
    await expect(component.getByTestId('loading-spinner')).toBeVisible();
  });

});
